Package polyglot.visit

Class Translator

java.lang.Object
polyglot.visit.PrettyPrinter
polyglot.visit.Translator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, Copy<Translator>
Direct Known Subclasses:
JL5Translator, TypedTranslator
public class Translator
extends PrettyPrinter
implements Copy<Translator>
A Translator generates output code from the processed AST. Output is sent to one or more java file in the directory Options.output_directory. Each SourceFile in the AST is output to exactly one java file. The name of that file is determined as follows:
  • If the SourceFile has a declaration of a public top-level class "C", file name is "C.java". It is an error for there to be more than one top-level public declaration.
  • If the SourceFile has no public declarations, the file name is the input file name (e.g., "X.jl") with the suffix replaced with ".java" (thus, "X.java").
To use: 
 new Translator(job, ts, nf, tf).translate(ast);
The ast must be either a SourceFile or a SourceCollection.
